{
    "publish_date": "2013-12-10T11:53:36.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT2M54S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": " (GASPS) ", 
            "dur": "1.16", 
            "start": "1.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " So, what is empathy and why is it \n VERY different than sympathy? ", 
            "dur": "5.24", 
            "start": "9.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Empathy fuels connection. ", 
            "dur": "2.52", 
            "start": "14.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Sympathy drives disconnection. ", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "17.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " It&#39;s very interesting. ", 
            "dur": "1.96", 
            "start": "20.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Theresa Wiseman is a nursing scholar ", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "22.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " who studied very diverse professions \n where empathy is relevant ", 
            "dur": "3.84", 
            "start": "25.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " and came up with \n four qualities of empathy. ", 
            "dur": "2.48", 
            "start": "29.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Perspective taking - ability to take \n the perspective of another person, ", 
            "dur": "4.04", 
            "start": "31.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " or recognise their perspective \n as their truth. ", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "35.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Staying out of judgment - ", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "38.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " not easy when you enjoy it \n as much as most of us do. ", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "40.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " (AUDIENCE CHUCKLES) ", 
            "dur": "1.6", 
            "start": "42.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Recognising emotion in other people, \n then communicating that. ", 
            "dur": "3.56", 
            "start": "44.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Empathy is feeling WITH people. ", 
            "dur": "3.32", 
            "start": "48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " I always think of empathy \n as this kind of sacred space. ", 
            "dur": "4.88", 
            "start": "51.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " When someone&#39;s in a deep hole \n and they shout from the bottom... ", 
            "dur": "4.36", 
            "start": "56.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " ..And we look and we say, &quot;Hey!&quot; \n And climb down... ", 
            "dur": "4.36", 
            "start": "64.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Sympathy is, &quot;Ooh!&quot; \n (LAUGHTER) ", 
            "dur": "3.08", 
            "start": "72.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " &quot;It&#39;s bad, uh-huh?&quot; \n (LAUGHTER) ", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "75.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " &quot;Uh... No. You want a sandwich?&quot; ", 
            "dur": "3.36", 
            "start": "78.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Empathy is a choice \n and it&#39;s a vulnerable choice. ", 
            "dur": "2.88", 
            "start": "84.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " In order to connect with you, ", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "87.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " I have to connect with something \n in myself that knows that feeling. ", 
            "dur": "4.56", 
            "start": "89.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Rarely, if ever, does an empathic \n response begin with, &quot;At least...&quot; ", 
            "dur": "5.44", 
            "start": "94.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " (LAUGHTER) ", 
            "dur": "1.96", 
            "start": "99.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Yeah. And we do it all the time \n because, you know what? ", 
            "dur": "3.4", 
            "start": "101.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Someone shared something with us \n that&#39;s incredibly painful ", 
            "dur": "3.28", 
            "start": "105.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " and we&#39;re trying \n to &quot;silver lining&quot; it. ", 
            "dur": "2.28", 
            "start": "108.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " I don&#39;t think that&#39;s a verb, \n but I&#39;m using it as one. ", 
            "dur": "3.2", 
            "start": "111.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " We&#39;re trying to put a silver lining \n around it. ", 
            "dur": "2.16", 
            "start": "114.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " So, &quot;I had a miscarriage.&quot; ", 
            "dur": "1.92", 
            "start": "116.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " &quot;At least you know \n you can get pregnant.&quot; ", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "118.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " &quot;I think my marriage \n is falling apart.&quot; ", 
            "dur": "2.04", 
            "start": "121.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " &quot;At least you have a marriage.&quot; ", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "123.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " (LAUGHTER) ", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "125.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " &quot;John&#39;s getting kicked out \n of school.&quot; ", 
            "dur": "2.2", 
            "start": "128.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " &quot;At least Sarah is an A-student.&quot; ", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "131.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " One of the things we do sometimes ", 
            "dur": "1.84", 
            "start": "133.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " in the face of very difficult \n conversations ", 
            "dur": "4.52", 
            "start": "135.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " is we try to make things better. ", 
            "dur": "2.12", 
            "start": "139.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " If I share something with you that&#39;s \n very difficult, I&#39;d rather you say, ", 
            "dur": "4.6", 
            "start": "142.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " &quot;I don&#39;t even know what to say. \n I&#39;m just so glad you told me.&quot; ", 
            "dur": "4.36", 
            "start": "146.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " Because the truth is, rarely can \n a response make something better. ", 
            "dur": "4.56", 
            "start": "151.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": " What makes something better \n is connection. ", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "156.04"
        }
    ], 
